title: Election for رئیس‌جمهور ایران / Rayis Jomhur-e Irān (Iranian President)
description:
Sourced from predicthq.com - At Stake in this Election:

The Presidency of Iran

The first round of this election was held on 28 June 2024.
Government Structure: 

Chief of State: Supreme Leader Ali Hoseini KHAMENEI (since 4 June 1989)
Head of Government: Acting President Mohammed MOKHBER (since 20 May 2024)
Assembly: unicameral Islamic Consultative Assembly (مجلس شورای اسلامی) with 290 seats

Electoral System: 

The Supreme Leader is appointed for life by the Assembly of Experts.
The President is directly elected by absolute majority vote in up to two rounds. The President may serve up to three 4-year terms, but only two terms may be served consecutively.
In the Islamic Consultative Assembly, 285 members are directly elected by absolute majority vote in up to two rounds. An additional 5 seats are reserved for representatives of the Zoroastrian, Jewish, Assyrian, Chaldean Christian, northern Armenian, and southern Armenian communities (1 seat each).  

Last Election:
The last presidential election was held on June 16, 2021. Ebrahim RAISI won with 18,021,945 votes (72.35%) and Mohsen REZAEE received 3,440,835 votes (13.81%). All other candidates received less than 10% of the vote. Voter turnout was 48%.
New/Unique this Election:
 This is a snap election, which was called following the death of President Ebrahim RAISI in a helicopter crash on 19 May 2024.
Key Deadlines:

Candidate filing deadline: 3 June 2024
Voter registration deadline: None, all citizens who are at least 18 years old may vote.

Candidates in this Election:

Massoud PEZESHKIAN
Saeed JALILI

An additional 5 seats are reserved for representatives of the Zoroastrian, Jewish, Assyrian, Chaldean Christian, northern Armenian, and southern Armenian communities (1 seat each).  

Last Election:
In the 2019 legislative election, the United Front of Conservatives won a majority with 230 seats (221 seats in the first round).  Voter turnout was 42%.
Key Deadlines:

Candidate filing deadline: 3 November 2023
Voter registration deadline: None, all citizens who are at least 18 years old may vote.

Candidates in this Election:
Second round elections will take place for 22 constituencies, comprising 45 seats in total. 90 candidates will contest these races.
